dcterms:description: The Marshall-Olkin extended exponential distribution is used to model aggregate claim amounts from two heterogeneous portfolios.
dcterms:title: Marshall-Olkin extended exponential distribution

L. Benkherouf
dcterms:description: The Harris family of distributions is introduced based on probability generating functions and is used in the context of stochastic comparisons.
dcterms:title: Harris family of distributions

M. Ganji
H. Bevrani
dcterms:description: The Lomax-exponential distribution is a model for right-skewed populations and is applied to claim amounts in portfolios of risks.

dcterms:creator: E.J. Gumbel
dcterms:description: The Gumbel-Hougaard survival copula is used to model dependencies in survival analysis and is referenced in the context of stochastic comparisons.

dcterms:creator: D.G. Clayton
dcterms:description: The Clayton copula is a model for association in bivariate life tables and is applied in epidemiological studies.

dcterms:title: Proportional hazard rate (PHR) model

dcterms:description: The PRHR model is a flexible family of distributions used in reliability theory and actuarial science.
dcterms:title: PRHR model

dcterms:creator: R.B. Nelsen
dcterms:description: Archimedean copulas are a class of copulas that provide a wide range of dependence structures.
